There are excellent open-source or VSCodium-friendly alternatives:

    Codeium (Not a typo, similar name!): This is the most popular AI for VSCodium. It offers a free tier for individuals that includes autocomplete and a Chat sidebar very similar to what you saw in the video. It works perfectly in VSCodium because they have a dedicated extension in the Open VSX registry.

    Continue: An open-source extension that lets you plug in your own AI models (like Claude, GPT-4, or even local models running on your Mac Mini).

    Supermaven: Known for being extremely fast, it also has a VSCodium-compatible extension.

The Verdict

    If you want the exact "official" experience from the video (GitHub Copilot): You would need to download the official "Visual Studio Code" (the blue icon version) from Microsoft.

    If you want to stay "De-Microsofted": I highly recommend searching your VSCodium extensions for "Codeium" or "Continue." You'll get nearly identical features (code explanations, refactoring help, and ghost-text completion) without the licensing headaches.




